      "kind": "concept",
      "name": "The Fall of the Luminous Souls",
      "archetypes": [
        "dualism"
      ],
      "gloss": "The cosmogonic event where primordial souls, originally dwelling in divine light, doubted the absolute divinity of 'Ali. This doubt caused their fall into the material realm of darkness, generating the physical universe as a temporary, purgatorial prison.",
      "facet": "Merges Shi'ite loyalism with Gnostic cosmogony: the material world is not a deliberate, 'good' creation by Allah, but a direct consequence of ontological ignorance and doubt.",
