      "tradition": "arabian",
      "kind": "deity",
      "name": "Almaqah",
      "archetypes": [
        "lunar",
        "sky-father"
      ],
      "gloss": "The moon-god and national deity of the Sabaeans of Saba, lord of the great temple at Marib (Awwam) — the bull-horned patron whose people called themselves 'the children of Almaqah'.",
      "facet": "The South-Arabian inversion of the Mediterranean sky: here the MOON is the supreme state-god and patriarch, the lunar power raised to the place a sun- or sky-father holds elsewhere.",
