      "gloss": "The great goddess of grain who, in her devastating grief over her daughter's abduction, deliberately withheld the harvest, plunging the world into famine until Zeus was forced to intervene and broker Persephone's return.",
      "facet": "Unlike the serene Olympian, the Eleusinian Demeter walked the earth as an old woman in mourning. She is a goddess of active refusal, wielding cosmic starvation to bend the patriarchal heavens to a mother's will.",
