      "facet": "His death does not redeem the world from sin; rather, it serves as a moral and initiatory drama where the candidate personally rehearses his murder and raising to learn the necessity of integrity over life.",
      "provenance": "Central to the Master Mason degree (first exposed in Samuel Prichard's 'Masonry Dissected', 1730); an extreme elaboration of brief biblical mentions in 1 Kings 7 and 2 Chronicles 2."
