      "gloss": "The supreme being invoked as the ultimate geometer, builder, and grand master of the cosmos. It functions as a deistic unifier that requires belief in a creator but leaves specific theological dogma entirely to the individual.",
      "facet": "It depersonalizes the divine into a structural principle, shifting the spiritual focus from appeasing a jealous deity to harmonizing oneself with universal, legible mathematical and moral laws.",
      "provenance": "Formalized in James Anderson's 'Constitutions of the Free-Masons' (1723); rooted in Enlightenment deism and Renaissance Hermetic-Pythagorean philosophy."
