      "facet": "The tradition boldly admits its own incompletion—the highest secret it offers is the revelation that the true secret has been lost, compelling the initiate to become a lifelong seeker rather than a fully enlightened master.",
      "provenance": "Central motif of the Master Mason and Royal Arch degrees; heavily influenced by Jewish mysticism and Kabbalistic notions of the Tetragrammaton."
