      "facet": "Death is not introduced as a divine punishment for sin or a trick by an evil spirit, but as a deliberate, pragmatic choice by a cultural hero to prevent overpopulation and stagnation.",
      "provenance": "Martin Gusinde, 'Die Selk'nam' (1931); Anne Chapman (1982)."
