      "name": "Fana (Annihilation in the Beloved)",
      "archetypes": [
        "ecstatic-shaman"
      ],
      "gloss": "The mystical Sufi state of 'annihilation' in God, where the seeker's individual ego and will are entirely subsumed into the divine presence, achieved through intensive dhikr (remembrance) and ascetic discipline.",
      "facet": "It dances on the razor's edge of orthodoxy. While adhering to strict monotheism, it insists the ultimate realization of Tawhid is the obliteration of the 'I'—not becoming God, but realizing the individual self was always an illusion masking the One.",
