      "gloss": "The obligatory pilgrimage to Mecca, ritually reenacting the trials of Abraham, Hagar, and Ishmael. Pilgrims gather on the plain of Arafat in a vast rehearsal of the Day of Judgment.",
      "facet": "It enforces a radical, physical egalitarianism. Kings and paupers wear the exact same unstitched white cloth, anchoring an abstract, transcendent monotheism to extreme physical exertion, heat, and visceral geographic specificity.",
