      "tradition": "modern-druidry",
      "kind": "deity",
      "name": "The Earth Mother",
      "archetypes": [
        "great-mother"
      ],
      "gloss": "The foundational maternal deity of the land and soil. She is typically invoked first in ritual as the ground of all being, the ultimate provider of the resources necessary for sacrifice and sustaining life.",
      "facet": "She is addressed not merely as an abstract mythic creator, but as the literal, localized biosphere the practitioner stands upon, fusing ancient mythology with modern ecological consciousness.",
