      "kind": "deity",
      "name": "Cernunnos (The Horned God)",
      "archetypes": [
        "master-of-animals"
      ],
      "gloss": "The antlered god of the wild, animals, wealth, and the deep forest. He embodies the untamed, fertile, and instinctual aspects of the natural world and vibrant masculine energy.",
      "facet": "He represents a vision of power entirely divorced from conquest or rulership, focusing instead on fierce stewardship, wildness, and the protective vitality of the woodland ecosystem.",
