      "kind": "concept",
      "name": "The Higher Self",
      "archetypes": [
        "one-through-many"
      ],
      "gloss": "The uncorrupted, omniscient fractal of the individual soul that resides permanently in the higher dimensions, untouched by earthly trauma, acting as the ultimate inner guru.",
      "facet": "Radically flattens the spiritual hierarchy by locating the supreme divine authority entirely within human consciousness, bypassing priesthoods, scriptures, and external saviors.",
      "provenance": "Jungian psychology; New Thought; channeled texts like Helen Schucman's 'A Course in Miracles'."
