      "gloss": "The doctrine that spiritual opulence inevitably manifests as material wealth. Because the Divine Mind is infinitely abundant, poverty is seen as a manifestation of mental restriction, while wealth demonstrates spiritual alignment.",
      "facet": "Eradicates the ascetic tradition completely. Poverty is never a virtue, trial, or badge of holiness, but a spiritual failure—effectively sacralizing American wealth as proof of divine mechanics.",
