      "kind": "deity",
      "name": "The Feathered Serpent",
      "archetypes": [
        "cosmic-serpent"
      ],
      "gloss": "The earliest known iteration of the pan-Mesoamerican plumed serpent, famously depicted on La Venta Monument 19. It combines the undulating, earth-bound body of a rattlesnake with the crest and feathers of a raptor, sheltering a human figure in its coils.",
      "facet": "It appears here not yet as the fully abstracted philosophical creator-god of later empires, but as a visceral, localized spirit of wind and flight—a literal, biological joining of the sky's apex and the earth's belly.",
