      "gloss": "A ubiquitous iconographic V-shaped notch or cleft, appearing on the heads of deities, celts, and stone altars. It represents the cosmic fracture from which maize originally sprouted and through which spiritual forces emerge from the underworld.",
      "facet": "It collapses the concepts of a cranial wound, an agricultural furrow, and a geological cave into a single geometric motif, transforming the physical rupture of the earth into the literal landscape of genesis.",
