      "facet": "Unlike the Olympian Dionysus of wine and frenzy, Zagreus is the innocent, sacrificed divine core whose brutal consumption forms the hidden, indestructible spark of divinity trapped within all human flesh.",
      "provenance": "Proclus, Commentary on Timaeus; Olympiodorus; Orphic fragments."
