      "gloss": "The 'things heard'—rigid, cryptic oral maxims governing daily life. They included strict prohibitions such as 'do not eat beans,' 'do not stir the fire with a knife,' and 'do not look in a mirror beside a lamp.'",
      "facet": "These seemingly arbitrary taboos fuse deep primitive superstition with philosophical symbolism, creating an all-encompassing way of life where every mundane action is fraught with cosmic risk.",
