      "archetypes": [
        "great-mother",
        "complementarity"
      ],
      "gloss": "The divine feminine counterpart to Jah, incarnate in Empress Menen Asfaw of Ethiopia. She represents the Mother of Creation, the balancing root of the earth, and the cosmic archetype of the righteous Black woman.",
      "facet": "While the movement can be highly patriarchal, Queen Omega establishes an inescapable divine dyad. King Alpha cannot rule without Queen Omega, rooting salvation in a married, historical African partnership rather than a solitary male deity.",
