      "archetypes": [
        "culture-hero",
        "genius-loci"
      ],
      "gloss": "The 'Great Mountain', an immensely powerful deity deeply involved in daily human affairs. Invoked for rain, successful harvests, and tribal protection, he is the active, territorial force in the pantheon, invariably associated with the highest local geological peak.",
      "facet": "He is both a majestic territorial god and the intimate cultural teacher who introduced brewing rice beer ('handia') and sexual intimacy to the first humans, bridging the sacred and the earthly joys.",
      "provenance": "J. Troisi (1978) 'Tribal Religion: Religious Beliefs and Practices among the Santals'."
