      "gloss": "The pervasive, impersonal spiritual energy and the innumerable specific spirits inhabiting rivers, forests, rocks, and households. Bongas can be benevolent or highly dangerous, demanding continuous propitiation and blood sacrifice from the community to maintain ecological and social equilibrium.",
      "facet": "'Bonga' blurs the line between distinct animistic personalities and a raw, electric-like force field of the landscape. They are not worshipped out of adoration, but negotiated with to maintain boundaries.",
