      "gloss": "The grey ash smeared across the forehead and body of the ascetic and the devotee. It is the ultimate residue left after the fire of spiritual knowledge has burned away all material attachments, desires, and illusions of the ego.",
      "facet": "It is an ever-present memento mori worn not in mourning, but in triumph. It declares that once everything superficial is reduced to ash, only the indestructible truth remains.",
