      "gloss": "A lamellophone consisting of forged iron keys bound to a wooden soundboard and amplified inside a calabash. Its cascading, cyclical polyrhythms are the literal 'telephone to the spirits.'",
      "facet": "The instrument is alive. The iron is forged from the earth, and the repetitive, interlocking melodies dissolve the human perception of linear time, aligning the mind with the eternal present of the ancestors.",
