      "name": "Pontifices Dei Solis (The Priesthood of the Sun)",
      "archetypes": [
        "cosmic-order"
      ],
      "gloss": "A prestigious college of priests established by Emperor Aurelian in 274 CE to administer the state cult of Sol Invictus. Drawn from the highest ranks of the Roman senatorial elite, they elevated the sun god's administration to equal standing with traditional Roman priesthoods.",
      "facet": "The creation of this priesthood was a masterstroke of political integration. Aurelian institutionalized Sol into the heart of the ancient patrician establishment, cloaking a new monistic theology in conservative Roman tradition to avoid Elagabalus's earlier mistakes.",
      "provenance": "Inscriptions from Rome (CIL VI); Zosimus, Historia Nova; S.E. Hijmans, The Sun in the Art and Religions of Rome."
