      "gloss": "The core theological claim of historical Universalism: that a loving, infinite God could not subject any soul to eternal conscious torment. It insists that all souls, without exception, will eventually be reconciled to the divine and to one another.",
      "facet": "By extinguishing hell entirely, it dismantles the theology of existential terror and cosmic dualism. Religion's focal point shifts radically from post-mortem rescue to present-world healing and ethical obligation.",
