      "gloss": "The Great-Great-One who came first from uHlanga, the bed of reeds, and broke off humankind and cattle after him — at once the first man, the first ancestor, and the maker of the world's institutions and names.",
      "facet": "The shard where creator and ancestor are not two things but one: Unkulunkulu does not stand above the world like a sky-god — he is the eldest of the lineage itself, the first link of the ancestral chain. Divinity is not descended from heaven but ascended from the reed-bed of the dead.",
