      "gloss": "The primal source — a marsh of reeds, or a single great reed — from which Unkulunkulu and all things broke off and came forth, the undifferentiated origin out of which the differentiated world is snapped loose.",
      "facet": "Not an egg and not a sea but a REED: the Nguni image of origin is a stem that buds and breaks, so creation is figured as vegetal severance — life pinched off from a living source rather than hatched, dived-up, or spoken.",
      "provenance": "uHlanga / uthlanga in Callaway; the word means both 'source/origin' and 'reed', and the slippage between the two is itself the cosmogony."
